H0.text: Protostomes are the other division of bilaterians alongside deuterostomes.

H1.text: Protozoa are the other group into which bilaterians are divided, alongside deuterostomes.

H2.text: Progestins are the other group, besides deuterostomes, into which bilaterians are divided.

H3.text: Gymnosperms are the group that, together with deuterostomes, the bilaterians are divided into.

A4.text: Bilaterians are traditionally classified as either deuterostomes or protostomes, based on whether the blastopore becomes the anus or mouth.

A5.text: The deuterostomes traditionally include the echinoderms, hemichordates, chordates, and the extinct Vetulicolia. The protostomes include most of the rest, such as arthropods, annelids, molluscs, and flatworms.
